{"cursor":"6338","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n'Kindness' is the act or the state of being kind, being marked by good and\ncharitable behavior, pleasant disposition, and concern for others. It is known\nas a virtue, and recognized as a value in many cultures and religions (see\nethics in religion). Research has shown that acts of kindness does not only\nbenefit receivers of the kind act, but also the giver, as a result of the\nrelease of neurotransmitters responsible for feelings of contentment and\nrelaxation when such acts are committed. \n","linknr":285,"url":"Kindness","recorded":1362551589,"links":27,"instances":["personal_and_cultural","virtue"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Kindness|","Positive psychology","Human behavior","Giving","Virtue","Emotions"],"headings":["In philosophy","In religion","In psychoanalysis","In literature","History","See also","References","Further reading"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/01/Gift_giving_ceremony.jpg/220px-Gift_giving_ceremony.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/ce/Plutchik-wheel.svg/90px-Plutchik-wheel.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["charity","virtue"],["value","personal_and_cultural"]],"members":["value","charity"],"related":["Good_and_evil","Charity_(virtue)","Disposition","Virtue","Value_(personal_and_cultural)","Ethics_in_religion","Aristotle","List_of_emotions","Friedrich_Nietzsche","Knightly_Virtues","Seven_virtues","Seven_deadly_sins","Envy","Talmud","Paul_of_Tarsus","Love","I_Corinthians","Paul_of_Tarsus","Buddhism","Paramitas","MettƒÅ","Tenzin_Gyatso,_14th_Dalai_Lama","Confucius","Basavanna","Kannada","Islam","Shakespeare","Robert_Louis_Stevenson","Altruism","Compa